snippet.textDisplay: Hard to say if that is a good buy or not on Rick’s part.  As a faceter, kunzite is not that hard to get, and not hard to get large.  That stone is really badly cut and would warrant a recut.  Kunzite has a lot of cleavage planes to deal with making cutting difficult, but I dont think I would consider it “rare”.  You don’t see a lot around because it is not as stable in color or durability as other options.  That stone was cut for weight, not to make it nice.  To bring that stone into correct angles you would need to take off a bit of material.
